===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
''{{w|Shuowen}}'': {{Han compound|尸|彳|夊|舟|ls=ic|t2=road|t3=foot|t4=(shoe-shaped) boat}}. Possibly {{liushu|psc|nocap=1|adj=1}}, with {{och-l|尸}} functioning as a phonetic component corrupted from {{och-l|眉}} which may also served as a phonetic component for {{och-l|履}}. Comparing Qin bamboo slip script, ''Shuowen'' seal's {{zh-l|*舟}} was corrupted from {{zh-l|*自}}, and Qin's 自 was simplified from {{zh-l|*頁}}.

{{w|Bronze inscriptions}}: {{Han compound|眉|頁|止|舟|ls=ic|t2=person with prominent head|t3=foot|t4=shoe or (shoe-shaped) boat}}.

Modern form is a compound of {{Han compound|尸|復|t2=return}}.

